@node WHAT_IS "What is UUCP2Fido"

        This  program  is  part  of  the  "Monalisa" project that
        consists  in  a  series of other programs that, together,
        can  perform  powerful  and  flexible  operations  within
        FidoNet  and other Networks.  Read Monalisa documentation
        for more details.

        Fido2UUCP  is  a  message  standard  converter.   It will
        convert Fidonet Echomail to Usenet Newsgroups.  It can be
        used  with  any  Fidonet  Mailer,  be it from a BBS, or a
        Point  setup.   The  UUCP  package must acceptr the RNews
        Batch  format.   C  News  and  Amiga UUCP V1.16 or higher
        accept these.
@endnode
@node HOW_DOES_IT_WORKS "How does it works"

        Fido2UUCP  is  a  pack  of two programs.  A Configuration
        module  with GUI and a Tosser.  The Tosser will scan your
        Fidonet  OutBound  directory for packtes to a pre-defined
        fake  system.   It  will  then  uncompress  the  packets,
        convert  the  messages  in it and re-pack them in a RNews
        Batch file.

        The  fake  system  is, in all, the system used to Gateway
        your EchoMail.  So you can still use your favorite mailer
        to propagate the conferences.  For instance, imagine that
        you  want to gate the conference AMIGA_INT.  All you have
        to  do  is  tell  your  system  mailer  to  activate that
        conference  for  the  fake  system  address.  Your mailer
        will,  of  course,  create  the  packets  for  it  in the
        OutBound   directory.    These   packets  will  never  be
        transmited  by  your  FrontDoor but instead, they will be
        used by Fido2UUCP.

        This  may  seem a bit dificult to understand at first but
        with  some  experience you'll find Fido2UUCP an extremely
        easy  and flexible tool to use.  Also, because of the way
        it   works,   it's   extremely   compatible   with   most
        configurations.
@endnode
